A. Relaxation curves of potato cylinders pretreated for different times with ultrasound. The continuous lines represent the experimental data and the shade region represent the confidence bands with 95% of confidence B. Effect of ultrasound pretreatment time on the maximum stress that the potato cylinders can support. C. Effect of ultrasound pretreatment time on the viscoelastic modulus parameter (k) from the model proposed by Guo and Campanella (2017) (Eq. (1)) of potato cylinders. D. Effect of ultrasound pretreatment time on the fractional order parameter (

                           α

                     ) from the model proposed by Guo and Campanella (2017) (Eq. (1)) of potato cylinders. In B., C. and D., dots represent the experimental data and vertical bars the standard deviation. Upper-case letters indicate the mean comparison (Tukeýs test p < 0.05) between the pretreatment with and without ultrasound and lower-case letters indicate the mean comparison among pretreatment times.
